# Vercel Speed Insights Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for this Vite + React project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` package (version added to dependencies)
- Updated `package.json` and `package-lock.json` accordingly

### 2. Code Integration
**Modified: `frontend/src/App.jsx`**
- Added import statement: `import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/react'`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component to the AppContent component alongside the existing `<Analytics />` component

## Implementation Details

Following the official Vercel documentation (https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart), I:

1. Used the React-specific integration path (`@vercel/speed-insights/react`)
2. Placed the SpeedInsights component at the app root level within the AppContent component
3. Positioned it alongside the existing Analytics component for consistency
4. Preserved all existing code structure and functionality

## Verification

- Build completed successfully with no errors
- TypeScript compilation passed
- All existing functionality preserved
- The SpeedInsights component will automatically begin tracking Core Web Vitals once deployed to Vercel and Speed Insights is enabled in the dashboard

## Next Steps

To complete the setup:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Navigate to the Vercel dashboard and enable Speed Insights for this project
3. Once enabled, the Speed Insights dashboard will begin collecting and displaying performance metrics

The implementation follows Vercel's best practices for React applications and integrates seamlessly with the existing Vercel Analytics setup.
